@startuml nav_and_failsafe_context_to_ibox_route_service_flags_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Nav And Failsafe Context To IBOX Route Service Flags Signal Flow\n(vehicle/nav context + fail-safe state -> IBOX link, route, and service-flag aggregation)

participant "Vehicle state bus" as Veh #F4F7FB
participant "Navigation buses" as Nav #E8F0FE
participant "ADAS/fail-safe context" as CoreCtx #FCE8FF
participant "IBOX\nconnectivity aggregator" as IBOX #E8F7E8
participant "IBOX runtime state" as IboxState #FFF4CC
participant "Observers /\nservice readers" as Obs #FFF4CC

== IBOX Inputs ==

Veh -> IBOX : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\ngVehicleSpeed / gDriveState
Nav -> IBOX : frmNavModuleStateMsg\nNavRouteClass / NavGuideType /\nNavEtaMinutes / NavSpeedLimit
Nav -> IBOX : frmNavigationRouteMsg\nEtaMinutes
CoreCtx -> IBOX : frmAdasDomainStateMsg\nSelectedAlertLevel
CoreCtx -> IBOX : CoreState::domainBoundaryStatus /\nwarningPathStatus and Core::failSafeMode
activate IBOX
IBOX -> IBOX : veh/nav freshness windows
IBOX -> IBOX : routeActive = roadZone > 0
IBOX -> IBOX : diagStage = ethDiagBoundaryStage(...)\nfrom route/alert/boundary/fail-safe
IBOX -> IBOX : linkMode = 0/1/2\nfrom freshness + service context
IBOX -> IBOX : routeState = 0/1/2\nfrom route class, nav direction, zone distance
IBOX -> IBOX : serviceFlags bitfield from\nroadZone / alertLevel / diagStage / overspeed
note right of IBOX
Representative gating inputs
- NavRouteClass / NavGuideType
- NavEtaMinutes / NavSpeedLimit
- gVehicleSpeed
- SelectedAlertLevel
- domainBoundaryStatus / failSafeMode
end note

== IBOX Runtime Publication ==

IBOX -> IboxState : runtime linkMode / routeState /\nserviceFlags / signalBars
note right of IBOX
Representative outputs
- linkMode
- routeState
- serviceFlags
- signalBars
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

IboxState -> Obs : connectivity and route-service visibility /\nreview and observer consumption
deactivate IBOX

note over Veh, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Vehicle, navigation, alert, and fail-safe context reach IBOX
2. IBOX evaluates freshness and route activity
3. IBOX derives link mode, route state, and service flag aggregation
4. IBOX exposes the final runtime service posture to observers
end note

@enduml
